<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="721" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d721">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.00/50</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-30T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>653. Your 1707 and 1688.<note n="1" xml:id="d721fn1">Latter not
                                printed.</note> Department has advised Finnish Commissioners here
                            that it approves of initial shipment of 2,000 tons of foodstuffs for
                            Finland. British Government does not object.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>